== English ==
=== Etymology ===
The use as a proper noun stems from the use of [[Baloo]] as a character name in [[w:Rudyard Kipling|Rudyard Kipling]]'s [[w:Jungle Book|Jungle Book]].  The character is a bear and is simply named from the {{Hind.}} '''[[भालू]]''' ''(bhālū,'' [[bear]]).

=== Proper noun ===
[[Category:English proper nouns]]
'''Baloo'''
# a [[given name]] 
#:'''usage note''': Usually it is a given name for animals, in particular pets, not for people.

